#RalphLauren #SS20

Color, perfected. #RLPurpleLabel's striking hues of silk shantung are custom-dyed in a centuries-old, family-owned Italian mill. Producing an exceptional luxury fabrication renowned for its sensuous drape and ideal for Purple Label's gracefully structured suiting.

Also featuring the RL 867 timepiece inspired by #RalphLauren’s Madison Avenue men’s flagship in New York City.

Discover the Purple Label Spring 2020 collection at our Ralph Lauren flagship stores.

#SS20

For spring, #RLPurpleLabel paints a vision of style in high-contrast colors of rare silk shantung. A custom-woven fabric that leaves the natural imperfections of its silk yarns intact, adding a unique charm to the finished cloth.

Discover the Purple Label Spring 2020 collection at our Ralph Lauren flagship stores.

#RalphLauren #SS20

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Starring #FeliceNovaNoordhoff in a signature #RalphLauren pairing of a tuxedo jacket and jeans. Tailored in lustrous, pearlescent charmeuse with prominent peak lapels, a structured shoulder line, and double-breasted cut. Worn with a floral-embroidered tulle blouse and embellished denim in a cropped, workwear-inspired silhouette rich with handmade appliqués.

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Starring #FeliceNovaNoordhoff in the Katherine jacket. Cut in Italian stretch wool with an exquisitely hand-embroidered crest rendered from velvet, grosgrain, and bullion.

Discover more from #RLCollection Spring 2020 via bio link.

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Starring #MalikaElMaslouhi in contrasts of cream-on-cream textures. Combining a lacquered linen trench coat with a silk turtleneck and wool gabardine trouser. And #Faretta in layers of vintage menswear-inspired patterns, from graphic checks to cricket and awning stripes in indigo, navy, and cream.

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Starring #FeliceNovaNoordhoff in new tailoring reimagined from the traditions of 1930s menswear. Including a high-waisted pant with authentic vintage details, from the double-pleated front and cuffed leg to the exaggerated waistband with concealed buttons for fastening suspenders. Worn with French blue striped shirting and a paisley necktie.

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Starring #FeliceNovaNoordhoff in a wool crepe evening top transformed from the elements of a formal vest and tailcoat. Worn with a sweeping, wide-leg satin pant and the new collection's Edwardian-inspired jewelry in crystal and sterling silver.

#RalphLauren

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Presenting The Spring 2020 Collection. "I think there's a degree of acting in fashion. You play different roles with your clothes... That's when the clothes come alive." — Ralph Lauren

Two expressions of #RalphLauren's lens on spring dressing, worn by #FeliceNovaNoordhoff and #Faretta. From the softly structured ease of a wool windowpane jacket and striped silk shirt to the elegant simplicity of a silk ballet-neck sweater and linen skirt.

Discover more from #RLCollection Spring 2020 via bio link.

#RalphLauren

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Presenting The Spring 2020 Collection. "I always wanted to make movies, but I'm just doing them in a different way, creating dreams." — Ralph Lauren

The romance of cotton eyelets, intricate floral embroidery, and delicately scalloped edges. Captured in a contemporary update to an antique silhouette influenced by the style of American prairies and homesteads. Worn by #FeliceNovaNoordhoff.

Discover more from #RLCollection Spring 2020 via bio link.

#RalphLauren

A Cinematic Vision of Style. Presenting The Spring 2020 Collection. "When I design a collection, I have a heroine in mind. She is the star of my movie and expresses what I have to say. I study her character, and I create for her and through her." — Ralph Lauren

Featuring #FeliceNovaNoordhoff in a double-breasted pinstripe jacket tailored in Italy from a lightweight blend of cotton, linen, and silk. Layered with a bow-neck cotton blouse in bold, vintage-inspired stripes. And #ChiharuOkunugi in the new collection’s lacquered cotton twill tuxedo and classic wingtip shirt.

Before #JanelleMonae took the #Oscars2020 stage in a #RalphLauren tuxedo for her show-opening performance, she arrived at Hollywood's biggest night in a custom #RLCollection gown. The look combined lacquered silk lamé tulle with three sizes of faceted crystals, more than 168,000 in total, requiring 600 hours to embroider each by hand.

The Making of a Moment: An exclusive look at #JanelleMonae's custom #RalphLauren gown for #Oscars2020. The shimmering, fully embellished silhouette required more than 600 hours of expert hand-embroidery to adorn 168,000 crystals over lacquered silk lamé tulle.

#RLCollection #RLRedCarpet #MakingOfAMoment #Oscars #Oscars2020

#JanelleMonae opens the #Oscars2020 with #BillyPorter in a performance of her song “Come Alive (War Of The Roses)” wearing a custom #RalphLauren piqué bib tuxedo shirt, tuxedo pant, and silk satin cummerbund. "I remember getting my first Ralph Lauren tuxedo and tuxedo shirt and wearing it at the beginning of my career — and I'm still rocking it. I'm still on stages, going to concerts, galas, walking down the street in a classic Ralph Lauren tuxedo. I never feel out of style and at the same time I feel ahead of the time," she said at Ralph Lauren’s Fall 2019 Collection celebration, where she delivered a rendition of the same show-stopping song.
